The paper discusses the use of surveillance drones for detecting and localizing amateur drones, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of signal-strength-based localization, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also mentions the use of optimization techniques for positioning surveillance drones, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY).
